     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"EDE", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Particle identification by `E/Delta E` measurement"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The neutron pick-up reaction 20Ne(3He,4He)19Ne"
		,"at a beam energy of 21 MeV was used to populate"
		,"excited states in 19Ne. A position-sensitive focal"
		,"plane detector was used to detect the outgoing"
		,"reaction products that entered the spectrograph."]
	}
      ]
     ,"ANALYSIS":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["Alpha particles were selected by setting a software"
		,"gate on the energy loss vs front position spectrum."
		,"Peak positions and intensities for the alpha-particle"
		,"spectra at each angle were obtained by fitting"
		,"Gaussian peaks with a linear function to describe the"
		,"local background. The fitting was done using BayeSpec"
		,"code. Given a fitting region, a model consisting of a"
		,"linear background and a specified number of Gaussian"
		,"peak shapes (all with common widths) is fit to the"
		,"data. For all input parameters uninformative Gaussian"
		,"priors are used with the starting values for"
		,"positions and intensities obtained from the user"
		,"input. This simultaneous fit to the data naturally"
		,"accounts for any correlations between parameters, for"
		,"example, background intensity and peak intensity. The"
		,"result is a Gaussian fit to each of the peaks giving"
		,"the mentioned parameters for every one of them. This"
		,"is particularly useful to extract centroids and"
		,"counts when two (or more) peaks are very close to"
		,"each other, but within the resolution limit of the"
		,"detector."]
	}
      ]
